 
<p>
Right-wing Democrat Cuellar joined Republicans in proposing a law that
would allow companies to eliminate important workers' rights, by
extending the 
<a href="https://www.commondreams.org/news/2022/08/01/coalition-representing-24-million-workers-blasts-dangerous-cuellar-bill">piecework sweatshop economy to more kinds of work.</a>
<p>
This would also stop states from requiring better wages and
working conditions for existing gig-work companies such as 
<a href="https://www.stallman.org/uber.html">Uber</a>
<p>
and 
<a href="https://www.stallman.org/lyft.html">Lyft.</a>

 